parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distances, and accidents, especially on steep and bumpy roads.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the ABS system fails to engage
the vehicle experiences dangerous driving conditions
the vehicle's braking performance is compromised.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty seatbelt retractor can cause the seatbelt to become stuck in a locked position, making it difficult or impossible to use the seatbelt properly, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt retractor locks in position
the seatbelt will not extend or retract
the seatbelt requires considerable manipulation to extend or retract
the seatbelt is stuck in a locked position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended release of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or damage to property.
symptoms: The parking brake releases on its own after the driver has left the vehicle
without any warning or indication; the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly; the parking brake light on the dashboard may not illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column bolts can cause the steering wheel to jam or lock up, resulting in loss of vehicle control, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel suddenly locks up or becomes difficult to turn
the steering column becomes loose or wobbly
the bolts backing out of the tilt steering column
no warning signs or symptoms before the failure.
